.TH MNEMOSYNE-INGEST-ADD 1 "2026-06-23" "mnemosyne" "Mnemosyne CLI"
.SH NAME
mnemosyne ingest-add \- Add a file, directory, URL, or text to the knowledge graph.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmnemosyne ingest-add\fR [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Add a file, directory, URL, or text to the knowledge graph.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fBtarget\fR
File, directory, or URL to ingest
.TP
\fB\-\-text\fR
Inline text to ingest instead of a target path or URL
.TP
\fB\-\-domain\fR
Domain for ingestion (default: daily)
.TP
\fB\-\-scope\-id\fR
Attach a scope ID (e.g. session name) to ingested entities
.TP
\fB\-\-source\-channel\fR
Tag the ingestion source channel (default: cli)
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Show what would happen without writing to the knowledge graph
.TP
\fB\-\-wiki\-root\fR
LLM Wiki root (default: ~/mnemosyne/wiki)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-wiki\fR
Do not update Markdown LLM Wiki pages
.TP
\fB\-\-wiki\-excerpts\fR
Opt in to bounded, redacted source excerpts in wiki source pages
.TP
\fB\-\-examples\fR
Show ingestion examples and output format details
.SH SEE ALSO
mnemosyne(1)
